A needy 21-year-old man from Uriri got has returned to school. During a funeral in Konduru, Peter Otieno sought help from MP Mark Nyamita. He joined Form One in Konduru Mixed Secondary in 2011 and scored a D plain in last year’s KCSE exam. He has been doing menial jobs for Sh300 a day. On Monday, Otieno joined St Pius Uriri Secondary in Form Three. Hi father and step-mother are sickly. His mother died. Speaking to the Star on the phone yesterday Nyamita said when Otieno approached me I thought he wanted a handout. “I was surprised when he asked for a scholarship,” he said.